verbs.description: outshake (third-person singular simple present outshakes, present participle outshaking, simple past outshook, past participle outshaken)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To surpass in shaking; to shake more or better than.
examples: The Baby Grand Cafe is offering Rose Hardaway $1,500 to dance against La Bommie for the title of "Shake Dance Queen of '52." Bets are 7-5 that Bommie can outshake her.
